name: "Food-Talk" Nutrition Seminar
description:
Join us for a great time simply talking about "FOOD"! Our life is surrounded by it and in order to feel great and healthy, we need to truly understand what it does for us.

Since I discovered that I have Celiacs and several food allergies, my life has become dedicated to finding CLEAN, WHOLESOME FOODS to eat without feeling deprived.

My before and after photos and glow for LIFE are proof that you can EAT HEALTHY and not be miserable. Let me show you everything that I've learned at this nutrition seminar.

DATE: SUNDAY, December 8th
TIME: 2:00 - 3:30pm
WHERE: Caribou Coffee Minnetonka (HWY 101 & HWY 7)

Purchase of this listing reserves your spot. Spaces are limited!

name: Food Prep with Peanut
description:
Are you having trouble getting excited about your "CLEAN MEALS"? Maybe you would like an extra set of hands to create delicious combinations of healthy food that you can enjoy the rest of your week. 

2 hours of prep - $150 (Can also be split between 2-5 people)

My training client Kellie had been following my carb-cycling plan for 2 months and reached a point of needing more. She asked if I could come to your home and help her "PREP" meals for her week. I gave her a list of foods to have ready and within an hour we had prepared SHRIMP, FISH, CHICKEN, TURKEY MEATBALLS, GRILLED VEGETABLES, SALAD, SWEET POTATO PANCAKES, and even CHOCOLATE COVERED KIWIS! She was floored at how yummy and easy everything was.

"Thank you so much for coming to my house and showing me how to meal plan and food prep.  The workouts have been fun for me but the food part has been much harder as I usually don't enjoy cooking.  I wanted food variety while sticking to your carb cycling plan but I was intimated and unsure how to go about it on my own and I didn't want it to be too time consuming.  You showed me how easy it is to have variety and tasty food without feeling deprived!  Thanks for being my fitness and food coach!!!!"

Feel free to me any questions at bethanyjn@gmail.com

name: EASY CARB-CYCLING meal plan
description:
"Your carb cycling plan rocks! I am down over 2 lbs this week! The no carb day was much easier this week! Body seems to be getting used to it! I love it! Thank you for sharing! I feel like its coming together and I can really do this! I am at a weight now that I have not been for a very very long time and feel great! I just am so grateful you share these tips and help those of us just starting out! Thank you!" - Traci Slane 

Are you looking to manage or drop some weight to feel great and look your best? I have made a sample "carb-cyling" plan that shows you how I eat all year long, especially when I am prepping for a competition to drop 1 lb a week.

They say "abs are made in the kitchen" and it's true. My body has only seen these changes because of carb-cycling. This plan is set up for a very managable healthy lifestyle and you WILL shed bodyfat. Carb-cycling keeps your body guessing which will set your metabolism on fire. You WANT to feel hungry all of the time and the kicker is you should EAT ALL OF THE TIME!

My meal plan will show you samples of fun meals that I eat all of the time (I'm also gluten, dairy and soy free) Here is a sample meal:

Protein: Turkey Burger (no bread)
Veggie: Add salsa or tomato to burger/ side of green beans or snap peas or spinach salad
Carb: Salty: Corn Tortilla Chips OR Sweet: dark chocolate (serving size should be around 20-
25 carbs)
Fat: Add peanut butter to dk choc. OR avocado to turkey burger

After your purchase I will email you a document within 24-48 hours to have as your own resource. The 6 page plan has a week plan with 5 meals laid out for each day. I also include a shopping list  that includes what you need for the sampled meals. Once you have this plan you can always send me an email with questions and I will gladly help you along the way.

Stick to this easy "real life" plan that is NOT extreme and will allow you to treat yourself. You will lean out and build lean muscle if you're lifting regularly too! Who wouldn't love that!?

Bethany Nelson (aka Peanut)
Figure Universe PRO & Fitness Competitor
